Sentencas: Anode supported (Ni/YSZ-YSZ-LSM/YSZ) solid oxide fuel cells were tested and the degradation over time was monitored and analyzed by impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: Test conditions were chosen to focus on the anode degradation and all tests were operated at 750 degrees C. O-2 was supplied to the cathode and the anode inlet gas mixture had a high p(H2O)/p(H-2) ratio of 0.4/0.6.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density
Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: Cells were tested over a few hundred hours applying varying current densities (OCV, 0.75 A/cm(2) and 1 A/cm2).
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: To investigate the effects of possible impurities in the inlet gas stream on the anode degradation, tests were setup both with and without gas cleaning.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: Gas cleaning was done by passing the H-2 over porous nickel at room temperature.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: It was found that cleaning of the inlet H-2 gas more than halved the anode degradation under current load.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: For tests at OCV the increase in the Ni-YSZ charge transfer reaction resistance changed from similar to 0.10 Omega cm(2) to become negligible (below 0.002 Omega cm(2)) upon applying H-2 gas cleaning over the couple of hundred of hours of testing.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density

Sentencas: Both for tests with and without H-2 gas cleaning applied, it was surprisingly found that operating the solid oxide fuel cells at OCV prior to fuel cell testing provided fuel cell tests with minimal/negligible anode degradation compared to tests where fuel cell testing was started immediately after initial characterization of the cells.
Titulo: Ni/YSZ electrode degradation studied by impedance spectroscopy Effects of gas cleaning and current density
